PCOS/ PCOD (Polycystic Ovarian syndrome)Â is one of the most common female endocrine hormonal disorders, affecting up to 20% of women in their reproductive age, which leads to primary or secondaryÂ infertility. 

Causes of PCOS/PCOD

The exact cause of PCOS/PCOD is unknown but it may be relating to abnormal hormone levels.

Resistance to insulin
Hormone imbalance
Genetics
High levels of androgens
Increased levels of inflammation

Symptoms of PCOS/PCOD

When menstrual cyclesÂ are irregularÂ (Less than 9 cycles per year)
Scanty bleeding or heavy flow
Weight gain or difficulty to lose weight
Excessive hair growth on face
Acne on face and back
Thinning of scalp Hair
Thick or pigmentation of skin on neck
Irritability or depression

Secondary Disorders Developing Due to PCOSÂ 

Obesity
Infertility and Miscarriage
High blood pressure
Dyslipidaemia (high level of blood cholesterol)
Insulin resistance or type 2 diabetes
Thyroid disorders

PCOS Treatment in Ayurveda
